This issue is meant to discuss how we want to do modals. Should we:

1. Use Redux & `<ModalController />`
2. Use React 16 Portals

Dan Abramov has a lovely answer to implementing modals as the accepted answer here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35623656/how-can-i-display-a-modal-dialog-in-redux-that-performs-asynchronous-actions/35641680

However, `react-portal` and now it's implemented with `React.createPortal` is also viable (if you scroll down in the SO post, you'll see answers along those lines as well.

In all my React projects, I've used the former approach where you dump a `ModalController` at the top level of your app and dispatch redux actions which set state and the modals are rendered based on app state. One difficulty (though I think it's fairly simple to overcome) is making it extensible in a mono-repo structure.

I'm still feeling in favor of using the Redux approach and here's a sketch of what that would roughly look like:

```js
// core/actionTypes.js
const OPEN_MODAL = "CORE/OPEN_MODAL";
const CLOSE_MODAL = "CORE/CLOSE_MODAL";

// core/actions.js
const openModal = ({ modalType, modalProps }) => ({
  type: actionTypes.OPEN_MODAL,
  payload: { modalType, modalProps }
});
const closeModal = () => ({ type: actionTypes.closeModal });

// core/reducers.js
const modalType = (state = "", action) => {
  switch(action.type) {
    case actionTypes.OPEN_MODAL:
      return action.payload.modalType;
    case actionTypes.CLOSE_MODAL:
      return "";
    default:
      return state;
  }
}
const modalProps = (state = {}, action) => {
  switch(action.type) {
    case actionTypes.OPEN_MODAL:
      return action.payload.modalProps;
    case actionTypes.CLOSE_MODAL:
      return {};
    default:
      return state;
  }
};
const modal = combineReducers({ modalType, modalProps });

// core/components/modal-controller/index.js
class ModalController extends React.Component {
  getModal = () => {
    const { modalType } = this.props;
    switch(modalType) {
      case "core/about-modal":
        return AboutModal;
      default:
        return null;
    }
  };
  render() {
    const { modalProps } = this.props;
    const Modal = this.getModal();
    if (!Modal) {
      return null;
    }
    return (
      <ModalOverlay>
        <Modal {...modalProps} />
      </ModalOverlay>
    );
  }
}

// not-core/components/modal-controller/index.js
class ExtendedModalController extends ModalController {
  getModal = () => {
    const { modalType } = this.props;
    switch(modalType) {
      case "not-core/cool-modal":
        return CoolModal;
      default:
        return super(); // This is the magic.
    }
  };
}
```

